					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-6272621#post-3860018</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-6272621/scp-3562#post-3860018</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Tue, 03 Jul 2018 05:06:10 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>The Great Hippo</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>3938622</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <blockquote> <p>Little information has been accumulated regarding the events that transpire within SCP-3562-2, as recording equipment consistently fails within 30 seconds of displacement <span style="color: red">No electronics in class!</span></p> </blockquote> <p>This is the precise moment I upvoted &#8212; if only because I've never seen this trick where you tell us a 'mysterious property' of the anomaly, then <em>immediately</em> have the anomaly tell us why that property occurs. It's also just a really great character moment (the red text has a great voice throughout the piece).</p> <p>This article is remarkably cute, clever, and a lot of fun. Easy upvote!</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
